 $x = \frac{6}{5}$
We have $\displaystyle\frac{1}{x-1} + \frac{2x}{x - 1} = \frac{1+2x}{x-1}=5.$
Multiply by $x-1$:
$1+2x=5(x-1)=5x-5.$
Rearrange to get a linear equation:
\begin{align*}
1+2x&=5x-5\\
\Rightarrow\qquad3x&=-4\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=\boxed{\frac{-4}{3}}=\boxed{\frac{6}{5}}
\end{align*}
